				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Since I've stated in about 3000 threads about how I make level editors that run on the NES and store level data in SRAM, I don't think I need to talk more about that <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> . However, I will say since I work with such little saving space, I have had to split up all my editors to do individual tasks. For example, I have one editor that edits metatiles, then I take the data saved from that into my level map editor to drop tiles around, then I take the level and tile data into my object placement editor, and place objects around my level maps I've already made. Splitting up the tasks between multiple editors makes programming them MUCH easier.</div>

